tle=List of Registered Medical Practitioners (The online Register)|publisher=[[General Medical Council]] |accessdate=28 February 2014}}</ref> He leads a research group in cardiovascular genetics which has published over 100 publications including original research papers in journals such as ''Nature'', ''[[The Lancet]]'' and the ''New England Journal of Medicine''.<ref name=\"ace\">{{Cite journal | doi = 10.1038/30374| pmid = 9607758| year = 1998| last1 = Montgomery | first1 = H. E.| authorlink1 = Hugh Montgomery (geneticist)| title = Human gene for physical performance| journal = Nature| volume = 393| issue = 6682| pages = 221\u20132| last2 = Marshall | first2 = R.| last3 = Hemingway | first3 = H.| last4 = Myerson | first4 = S.| last5 = Clarkson | first5 = P.| last6 = Dollery | first6 = C.| last7 = Hayward | first7 = M.| last8 = Holliman | first8 = D. E.| last9 = Jubb | first9 = M.| last10 = World | first10 = M.| last11 = Thomas | first11 = E. L.| last12 = Brynes | first12 = A. E.| last13 = Saeed | first13 = N.| last14 = Barnard | first14 = M.| last15 = Bell | first15 = J. D.| last16 = Prasad | first16 = K.| last17 = Rayson | first17 = M.| last18 = Talmud | first18 = P. J.| last19 = Humphries | first19 = S. E.}}</ref><ref name=\"scopus\">{{Scopus|id= 35482685300}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal\n | pmid = 19129527\n| year = 2009\n| last1 = Grocott\n| first1 = M. P.\n| title = Arterial blood gases and oxygen content in climbers on Mount Everest\n| journal = New England Journal of Medicine\n| volume = 360\n| issue = 2\n| pages = 140\u20139\n| last2 = Martin\n| first2 = D. S.\n| last3 = Levett\n| first3 = D. Z.\n| last4 = McMorrow\n| first4 = R\n| last5 = Windsor\n| first5 = J\n| last6 = Montgomery\n| first6 = H. E.\n| author7 = Caudwell Xtreme Everest Research Group\n| doi = 10.1056/NEJMoa0801581\n| url = http://eprints.brighton.ac.uk/14342/1/NEJM%20CXE%20ABG%202009.pdf\n}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal | doi = 10.1016/S0140-6736(03)14286-9| pmid = 13678872| title = Efficacy of perindopril in reduction of cardiovascular events among patients with stable coronary artery disease: Randomised, double-blind, placebo-controlled, multicentre trial (the EUROPA study)| journal = The Lancet| volume = 362| issue = 9386| pages = 782\u2013788| year = 2003| last1 = Fox| first1 = K. M.| author2 = EURopean trial On reduction of cardiac events with Perindopril in stable coronary Artery disease Investigators}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal | doi = 10.1016/S0140-6736(09)60935-1| pmid = 19447250| title = Managing the health effects of climate change| journal = The Lancet| volume = 373| issue = 9676| pages = 1693\u2013733| year = 2009| last1 = Costello | first1 = A. | last2 = Abbas | first2 = M. | last3 = Allen | first3 = A. | last4 = Ball | first4 = S. | last5 = Bell | first5 = S. | last6 = Bellamy | first6 = R. | last7 = Friel | first7 = S. | last8 = Groce | first8 = N. | last9 = Johnson | first9 = A. | last10 = Kett | first10 = M. | last11 = Lee | first11 = M. | last12 = Levy | first12 = C. | last13 = Maslin | first13 = M. | last14 = McCoy | first14 = D. | last15 = McGuire | first15 = B. | last16 = Montgomery | first16 = H. | last17 = Napier | first17 = D. | last18 = Pagel | first18 = C. | last19 = Patel | first19 = J. | last20 = De Oliveira | first20 = J. A. P. | last21 = Redclift | first21 = N. | last22 = Rees | first22 = H. | last23 = Rogger | first23 = D. | last24 = Scott | first24 = J. | last25 = Stephenson | first25 = J. | last26 = Twigg | first26 = J. | last27 = Wolff | first27 = J. | last28 = Patterson | first28 = C. }}</ref>\n\nHe is a Professor of [[Intensive-care medicine|Intensive Care Medicine]] at UCL and practises as a consultant in critical care at the [[Whittington Hospital]] in north London.{{cn|date=September 2018}}\n\n==Other interests==\nMontgomery has been awarded the title of London Leader by the London Sustainable Development Commission for his work in climate change and health under the auspices of Project Genie; he was also a founding member of the UK Climate and Health Council and one of the co-authors of the UCL-Lancet Commission in 2009.\nMontgomery has complemented his interest in fitness with achievements which include the 100&nbsp;km [[ultramarathon|ultra marathons]], holding the world record for underwater piano playing as well as visiting [[Everest]] with the Xtreme Everest research group to undertake research.<ref name=\"everest\">{{Cite journal\n | pmid = 20586597\n| year = 2010\n| last1 = Grocott\n| first1 = M. P.\n| title = Caudwell xtreme Everest expedition\n| journal = High Altitude Medicine & Biology\n| volume = 11\n| issue = 2\n| pages = 133\u20137\n| last2 = Martin\n| first2 = D. S.\n| last3 = Wilson\n| first3 = M. H.\n| last4 = Mitchell\n| first4 = K\n| last5 = Dhillon\n| first5 = S\n| last6 = Mythen\n| first6 = M. G.\n| last7 = Montgomery\n| first7 = H. E.\n| last8 = Levett\n| first8 = D. Z.\n| author9 = Caudwell Xtreme Everest Research Group\n\n| doi = 10.1089/ham.2009.1093\n| doi-access = free\n}}</ref>\n\nHe is the co-Editor-in-Chief of the Open Access journal ''Extreme Physiology & Medicine'' published by [[BioMed Central]].<ref>{{Cite journal | doi = 10.1186/2046-7648-1-1| pmid = 23849731| pmc = 3707096| title = Extreme Physiology & Medicine: A new journal focussed on integrative human physiology under stress| journal = Extreme Physiology & Medicine| volume = 1| issue = 1| pages = 1| year = 2012| last1 = Grocott | first1 = M. P. | last2 = Montgomery | first2 = H. E. }}</ref>\n\nMontgomery is the author of the children's book ''[[The Voyage of the Arctic Tern]]''.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Gordon|first1=Bryony|title=I'm Always Adding Strings to mMy Bow|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/finance/4493031/Im-always-adding-strings-to-my-bow.html|accessdate=4 February 2017|agency=The Telegraph (U.K.)|date=11 June 2002}}</ref>\n\n==Awards and honours==\n*2007 Presented the televised annual [[Royal Institution Christmas Lectures]] on the subject ''Back from the brink: the science of survival''.<ref>[http://richannel.org/christmas-lectures/2007/hugh-montgomery Royal Institution Christmas Lectures 2007: ''Back from the brink: the science of survival'']</ref><ref>[http://www.richannel.org/ri-unconference-hugh-montgomery--science-and-the-environment, Hugh Montgomery address on Science & Environment], [[Royal Institution]] Unconference, September 2011</ref>\n*2010 Chosen to present the [[Ellison-Cliffe Lecture]] at the [[Royal Society of Medicine]].{{cn|date=September 2018}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n{{authority control}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Montgomery, Hugh}}\n[[Category:Academics of University College London]]\n[[Category:21st-century English medical doctors]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:1962 births]]\n[[Category:Alumni of the University of London]]\n[[Category:People from Plymouth]]\n[[Category:People educated at Plymouth College]]\n", "name_user": "Notreallydavid", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hugh_Montgomery_(physician)"}
{"title_page": "Palicoureeae", "text_new": "{{Automatic taxobox\n| image = \n| image_caption = \n| taxon = Palicoureeae\n| authority = Robbr. & Manen\n| type_genus = ''[[Palicourea]]''\n| type_genus_authority = [[Jean Baptiste Christophore Fus\u00e9e Aublet|Aubl.]]\n}}\n\n'''Palicoureeae''' is a [[Tribe (biology)|tribe]] of [[flowering plant]]s in the [[Family (biology)|family]] [[Rubiaceae]] and contains about 817 [[species]] in 11 [[genus|genera]]. Its representatives are found in the tropics and subtropics.<ref name=\"WCSP\">{{cite web|url=http://apps.kew.org/wcsp|title=World Checklist of Rubiaceae|accessdate=21 April 2016}}</ref>\n\n==Genera==\nCurrently accepted names<ref name=\"WCSP\"/><ref name=\"Robbrecht2006\">{{cite journal|vauthors=Robbrecht E, Manen JF |year=2006|title=The major evolutionary lineages of the coffee family (Rubiaceae, angiosperms). Combined analysis (nDNA and cpDNA) to infer the position of Coptosapelta and Luculia, and supertree construction based on rbcL, rps16, trnL-trnF and atpB-rbcL data. A new classification in two subfamilies, Cinchonoideae and Rubioideae|journal=Systematic Geography of Plants|volume=76|pages=85\u2013146}}</ref><ref name=\"Bremer2009a\">{{cite journal|author=Bremer B|year=2009|title=A review of molecular phylogenetic studies of Rubiaceae|journal=Annals of the Missouri Botanical Garden|volume=96|pages=4\u201326|doi=10.3417/2006197}}</ref><ref name=\"Bremer2009b\">{{cite journal|vauthors=Bremer B, Eriksson E |year=2009|title=Time tree of Rubiaceae: phylogeny and dating the family, subfamilies, and tribes|journal=International Journal of Plant Sciences|volume=170|pages=766\u2013793|doi=10.1086/599077}}</ref><ref name=\"Razafim2014\">{{cite journal|vauthors=Razafimandimbison SG, Taylor CM, Wikstr\u00f6m N, Pailler T, Khodabandeh A, Bremer B|year=2014|title=Phylogeny and generic limits in the sister tribes Psychotrieae and Palicoureeae (Rubiaceae): Evolution of schizocarps in Psychotria and origins of bacterial leaf nodu